text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described by Robert Chinnock in 2007 and the description was published in Eremophila and Allied Genera: A Monograph of the Plant Family Myoporaceae. The specific epithet (flaccida) is a Latin word meaning "drooping" referring to the hanging flowers of this species.There are two subspecies:

Eremophila flaccida Chinnock subsp. flaccida which has egg-shaped leaves with a distinct stalk;
Eremophila flaccida subsp. attenuata Chinnock which has linear to lance-shaped leaves which taper gradually towards the base and lack a distinct stalk.
